The paper deals with game theoretic approaches to optimizing outcomes in social computing applications, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of contests and rewards to incentivize contributions, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the role of effort and expertise in determining the value of contributions, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
